	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64516781"><p>I had a new programmer who started wanting to shift his hours, stopped showing up for meetings, and most telling, in three weeks, never completed a single ticket. I gave him the benefit of the doubt at first, then laid out some specific expectations, and finally fired him. After that termination call, HR told me "you did your job, he was not surprised."</p><p>The thing is, if you are paying attention, these things are not hard to spot.</p></div>
